    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/31562 added proper cursor shape and blink support, but unfortunately `cell_percentage` (in the `mode_info_set` event) is always set to 0, which makes the cursor invisible in GUIs like Neovide.\n\nThis was first reported here https://github.com/neovide/neovide/issues/2897\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Start neovide\n2. Open `:terminal` with a bash shell using the default vertical bar cursor shape\n3. Observe that the cursor is invisible\n\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim should set `cell_percentage` to something reasonable, for example `25` for the vertical bar and `20` for the vertical bar, like the `guicursor` defaults.\n\nAlternatively, it should be documented that 0 is GUI specific, and that the GUI can choose a suitable value. But in that case, it would probably make sense to set the `guicursor` default to 0 as well.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1399+gd1e00a5f6d\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nNeovide 0.13.3\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
