            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/31703 sets the default percentages to 25 and 20 for vertical and horizontal, respectively. This isn't configurable tho, it's hard coded.\n\n>Alternatively, it should be documented that 0 is GUI specific, and that the GUI can choose a suitable value. But in that case, it would probably make sense to set the guicursor default to 0 as well.\n\nI think this is worth considering too. As I mentioned in the PR, the escape sequences to set the cursor shape in the terminal can't specify things like \"cursor width\". So if we ever want this to be configurable, it will have to be configured at the UI level, in which case having a value for \"the UI decides the width\" would make sense.",
